The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, March 31: The inflation rate has declined to 4.06 per cent for the week ended March 18 from 4.28 per cent in the previous week. The slow down in wholesale price rise was mainly due to cheaper vegetables, poultry chicken, eggs, inland-fish, tea, fodder, edible oils and sugar. But wheat, bitumen, furnace oil, naphtha, milk powder, baby food, cigarettes, iron and steel, PVC pipe, and electrical equipment became costlier.

 Mumbai, March 31: The foreign exchange reserves of the country has increased by $2.503 billion to $148.662 billion during the week ended March 24 against $146.159 billion in the previous week. Foreign currency assets increased by $2.506 billion to $142.159 billion during the week. 

 Mumbai, March 31: The income tax department has served a notice to Hindustan Lever Limited as it faltered on payment of tax deducted at source. The dispute is regarding whether a company which outsources manufacturing should deduct TDS on payments it makes.

 New Delhi, March 31: Nasscom has tied up with the Dutch Centre for Promotion of Imports from developing countries to enable small and medium businesses in Europe to outsource work to India.

 New Delhi, March 31: A parliamentary panel has asked the government to formulate a common policy for disposal of surplus assets of the central PSUs.




